claim.claim-text:
A valve assembly comprising:
a shaft (10), the shaft comprising;
a sight through-hole (12); and
a flow through-hole (13);
the valve assembly further comprising a shaft position mechanism (20), the shaft position mechanism comprising;
a driving means (21) configured to provide movement to the shaft;
at least one emitter (23, 25) and at least one corresponding sensor (22, 24);
the valve assembly further comprising at least one flow path from at least one fluid inlet (41) to at least one fluid outlet (42, 43);
wherein the shaft (10) is configured to move across the at least one flow path so as to allow flow therethrough in a first position, and to block the at least one flow path in a second position;
wherein the at least one emitter (23, 25) and the at least one corresponding sensor (22, 24) are positioned such that, when the shaft is in the first position, the sensor (22, 24) can sense the emitter (23, 25) through the sight through-hole (12) of the shaft (10), and when the shaft is in the second position, the sensor (22, 24) is blocked from the emitter (23, 25) by the shaft (10).

The valve assembly of claim 1, wherein the at least one emitter comprises a first and a second emitter (23, 25), and the at least one corresponding sensor comprises corresponding first and second sensors (22, 24), and wherein the at least one fluid outlet comprises a first and a second fluid outlet (42, 43);

wherein the shaft (10) is further configured to move to a third position so as to allow flow from the at least one inlet (41) to the first outlet (42), and block flow from the at least one inlet (41) to the second outlet (43); and

wherein the first and second emitter (23, 25) and the corresponding first and second sensors (22, 24) are positioned such that;
when the shaft is in the first position, the first sensor (22) can sense the first emitter (23) through the sight through-hole (12) of the shaft (10), and the second sensor (24) is blocked from the second emitter (25) by the shaft; and
when the shaft is in the second position, the first and second sensors (22, 24) are blocked from the first and second emitter (23, 25) by the shaft (10); and
when the shaft is in the third position, the second sensor (24) can sense the second emitter (25) through the sight through-hole (12) of the shaft (10), and the first sensor (22) is blocked from the first emitter (23) by the shaft.

A system comprising;
the valve assembly of claim 9;
a control module (36); and
a power source, wherein the power source is configured to power the valve assembly and charge the supercapacitor (31), the supercapacitor (31) being configured to power the at least one emitter (23, 25) and the at least one sensor (23, 24) in case of failure of the power source.
